        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 14 at 9:29PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 929 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 18
miles southeast of White Sulphur Springs, moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Martinsdale, Checkerboard, and Lennep.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
